Open up https://www.oracle.com and download latest version of Virtual Box.

Get up to date on Virtual Box using the step-by-step lectures here: https://www.youtube.com/user/OracleLearning

Installing ubuntu

Finishing up - Install add-on Utils.

Basic CLI commands
  ls - list files in curent dir
  touch "file name" - creates and empty file with name "file name"
  mkdir "dir name" - create dir with name "dir name"
  nano "file name" - open file "file name" in nano text editor - ctrl-o, ctrl-x
  cat "file name" - displays the contents of the "file name" file to the console
  man man
  man "command" - command manual for other commands ex: man ls
  cd "path"- change dir - ex: cd Downloads, cd .., cd .
  pwd - present working dir ex: pwd - returns /home/username
  cp "point1" "point2" - copy file from point1 to point2 ex: cp ../test . || cp test /home/melania/public/test
  sudo - super user do - sudo apt update - run the apt update command as super user
  
  
Install Git

  protonmail - new email on protonmail
  github - new account on github
  install git on cli - apt install git

